    ],
    "generation": "A",
    "branch": "Rudy",
    "parent": null,
    "vitals": {
      "photo": "rudy.jpg",
      "deceased": true,
      "dateOfDeath": "2019-02-14",
      "obituary": "Rudolph \"Rudy\" Warshawsky, beloved husband, father, grandfather, and great-grandfather, passed away on February 14, 2019 at the age of 92 in West Palm Beach, Florida.\n\nRudy was an avid Yankees fan and loved anything to do with sports. He served our country with extraordinary valor in World War II as a member of the 101st Airborne Easy Company 506th — the legendary \"Band of Brothers\" — who parachuted into Normandy, France on June 6, 1944 on D-Day. He also served in the Korean War and received a Purple Heart for Bravery.\n\nHe is survived by his beloved wife Maxine; loving children Bruce (Debra) Warner, Lori (Glenn) Robertson and Helene Pry; cherished grandchildren Michael, Andrew, Hilary, Matthew, Kristen and Keith; and adored great-grandchildren Savannah, Kaitlyn, Logan, Kylie and Parker. He was predeceased by his grandson Daniel.\n\nHe will be missed by his loving family and close friends. We Love You Rudy!",
      "photoPanX": 0,
      "photoPanY": 50,
      "photoZoom": 1.0
    },
